title._content: President's House, Keene State College, Keene, NH

description._content: TITLE President's House, Keene State College, Keene, NH CREATOR Souvenir Post Card Co., New York NY SUBJECT Universities and colleges - NH - Keene Houses - NH - Keene DESCRIPTION Postcard of the Normal School Principals Residence, now the President's House, Keene State College located on Main Street in Keene New Hampshire. This was originally the Old Bond House and is located at 251 Main Street. It was built around 1805 by John G. Bond in the Federal style, as part of his 20 acre farm. From 1824 to 1844 it was used as Miss Catherine Fiske's Female Seminary. It became a private home again in 1845 and manufacturer Madison Fairbanks lived there and later Mr. and Mrs. Edward C. Thayer. This building and the Hale House were the two original buildings made available for Keene Normal School, later Keene State College, in 1909.
